This paper discusses the privacy implications of web browser fingerprinting, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also examines the user experience of using different browsers, which could be considered under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and programming languages (cs.PL) as different browsers may have different programming languages and interfaces. Finally, the paper discusses the technical aspects of collecting and analyzing browser data, which could be considered under social and information networks (cs.SI).
